    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Note by the Secretaries of the Combined Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 317/2</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quebec</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-22">22 August
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Equipping Allies, Liberated Forces and Friendly
                        Neutrals</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Action on <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 317<note n="1" xml:id="d465fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1029">p. 1029</ref>.</note>
                    has been deferred pending further study of the subject by the British Chiefs of
                    Staff.</p>
                <p>The United States Chiefs of Staff, however, recommend that immediate decision be
                    rendered on the recommendations contained in paragraph 10 <hi rend="italic"
                        >a</hi> and <hi rend="italic">b</hi> of that paper. These paragraphs pertain
                    to the equipment of French forces in North Africa. A decision at this time is
                    necessary because of certain administrative arrangements which should be carried
                    out at once in the event that the recommendations are to be approved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed> H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Redman</hi>
                        <lb/> J. K. <hi rend="smallcaps">Deane</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Combined Secretariat</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
